product_name: NYX Professional MakeupWonder Stick Cream Highlight & Contour Stick
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackHighlight, contour and blend like a wonder with the cream contour Wonder Stick from NYX Professional Makeup!
details: DetailsBenefitsShape, brighten and blend like a wonder with the fan favorite creamy Wonder Stick now in 8 shadesFeaturing contour and highlighter, this super face shaping duo sculps your face structure while mimicking a sunlit glowSmooth application and a buildable creamy formula allows you to customize your look with ease making this the perfect contouring stick for beginnersAvailable in 8 ultra-blendable color combinationsPartner this cream contour stick with the NYX Wonder Stick Cream Blush to achieve the rainbow contour technique100% vegan formula (no animal-derived ingredient or by-product)Cruelty freeItem 2595218How To UseFirst, swipe the deeper shade along the face's natural contours including the forehead, cheekbones & jawline, then apply the lighter shade to highlight the highest points of the face including the under eyes, middle of the forehead & chin. Blend well with a NYX Professional Makeup Pro Brush for a gorgeous finish! With both warm and cool undertones use a shade with a cool undertone to contour and a warm undertone as a bronzer.Pro Tip: Angle your lines upwards to create a lifted look!IngredientsEthylhexyl Palmitate, Cetearyl Ethylhexanoate, Paraffinum Liquidum / Mineral Oil / Huile Minerale, Synthetic Wax, Pentaerythrityl Tetraisostearate, Euphorbia Cerifera Cera / Candelilla Wax, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Hydrogenated Coconut Oil, Cera Microcristallina / Microcrystalline Wax / Cire Microcristalline, Silica Silylate, Ricinus Communis Seed Oil / Castor Seed Oil, Aluminum Hydroxide, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Tocopheryl Acetate, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain / Peut Contenir (+/-): Mica, CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide. Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Cetearyl Ethylhexanoate, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Isodecyl Neopentanoate, Dimer Dilinoleyl Dimer Dilinoleate, Synthetic Wax, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Cera Microcristallina / Microcrystalline Wax / Cire Microcristalline, Euphorbia Cerifera Cera / Candelilla Wax, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Ricinus Communis Seed Oil / Castor Seed Oil, Tin Oxide, Tocopherol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain / Peut Contenir (+/-): Mica, CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide.
how_to_use: First, swipe the deeper shade along the face's natural contours including the forehead, cheekbones & jawline, then apply the lighter shade to highlight the highest points of the face including the under eyes, middle of the forehead & chin. Blend well with a NYX Professional Makeup Pro Brush for a gorgeous finish! With both warm and cool undertones use a shade with a cool undertone to contour and a warm undertone as a bronzer.Pro Tip: Angle your lines upwards to create a lifted look!

reviews.headline: Could be me..
reviews.comments: It could be user error but I had a difficult time blending the product and the color just didn't look right on me even though it was lighter (I am fair skinned)

reviews.headline: Love the Duo!
reviews.comments: Its my go to for a contour and highlight. I love that its smooth and easy to use.

reviews.headline: not a fan
reviews.comments: it is cheaply made and maybe not for melanin skin.I could barely see it and it looked like I had just draw my face with a marker so when I rub it in it did nothing

reviews.headline: Hm
reviews.comments: Good product, but came heavily damaged, its a pain to use. I bought it because I liked the way it was a stick and easy to apply, but the highlighter and the contour both came broken.

reviews.headline: Very Potent Highlight/Bronzer
reviews.comments: A little of this product goes a long way.  It is creamy and easy to apply; however, the pigment is intense and takes a LOT of blending.  Even though I picked the shade labeled "for everyone", this is too orange/brown for my pale peachy skin.

reviews.headline: love the contour don't love the highlight
reviews.comments: The contour side is great! I thought that the shade was perfect for me; it contours without looking orange or muddy. It is also very blendable and easy to work with. With that said, I don't love the highlight. It is a weird gold color that is too dark for my skin tone. I also don't love the consistency for a highlighter and feel it goes on a bit streaky.

reviews.headline: I like itâ€¦
reviews.comments: I love this Wonder stick! It contours so well and is the perfect topper to my makeup routine. I only use one end, so I'm not sure how well the lighter end works for my skin tone.

reviews.headline: Absolutely love this product and will definitely buy again!
reviews.comments: The formula is so creamy and blends right into my skin! Best contour stick I've ever tried and for a very reasonable price.

reviews.headline: Acne Causer
reviews.comments: Wanted to love this product, but it broke me out severly. I noticed clusters of acne on areas where I apply this product, and have had no changes to makeup or diet or lifestyle that could lead me to the conclusion of something else causing the breakouts.

reviews.headline: I like the product just not the shade I got recommended
reviews.comments: I asked for help to find my shade, the one they recommended looks super dark on me.

reviews.headline: it's not my idea of a good value
reviews.comments: it may be affordable, but it won't blend as easily as a slightly higher price bronzer stick. save your money.

reviews.headline: My tried and true
reviews.comments: I've tried all kinds of sticks, none lint this formula!  It is outstanding!  I  don't care much for the highlight side of it, it's meh.  But the contour is the best ever!

reviews.headline: My go to
reviews.comments: My go to contour. Not a fan of golden shade so I go for the Fair option. I dont use the highlight at all but for the price is blends nicely

reviews.headline: So Amazing!! ðŸ˜»
reviews.comments: I love this product and it's half the price of some more expensive contouring / highlighting products. Staying power and it shows up well under foundation.

reviews.headline: Great product!!
reviews.comments: The contour blends so well and stays! It's a little orange for a contour, but I still love it for everyday use. The highlighter is great too, but harder to blend. Will probably repurchase

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: I really love it, thank you so much for considering me

reviews.headline: Go back to the OG
reviews.comments: This new formula is awful. I don't know why they changed it. The original was so much better. I hate how this one is half matte and half shimmer  while the OG was just matte and perfect to add shimmer if you want it. As well as it breaking so much easier. I broke it the first time I used it and I barely even had it twisted out but its so oily now, it was reletively easy to put it back together to use if i wanted :(

reviews.headline: Works well
reviews.comments:
I received this product for free as a tester. 

I really enjoyed how well this blended and the finish provided such great coverage. I'm not big on my makeup having scent and thankfully this one didn't have a strong fragrance.

reviews.headline: My new staple in my makeup routine
reviews.comments: I loveeeee this product!! It's so creamy , easy to blend , perfect color doesn't leave an orange or grey cast. You can blend with a brush or a sponge. I use this product everyday in my makeup routine now , it truly is a staple in my routine. I've tried a lot of cream contours and this is by far my favorite

reviews.headline: Product hits in the middle
reviews.comments: Love the dual end and how creamy it applies. But, after it's blended feel like it smears off easily even with setting spray. Works okay for the price. Think I might try something a little different next time.

faceoff_positive.comments: I made two purchases to get the right color (and it still isn't what I used to have). I matched the order to the colors on my current stick; yet when the new stick came it was so different from the original I had to return it. Return was easy and fast. Good customer service.
faceoff_positive.headline: Good product but they changed the color

faceoff_negative.comments: I'm so disappointed in the shade fair. I am Obviously very fair and have the hardest time finding cream contour as they all pull very yellow or even yellow green on me. This product pulled very warm Peachy brown on me. The highlight shade I think is slightly too dark for my complexion however I'll keep it for the highlight end so the product Doesn't go to waste :/
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointed with the shade fair
